			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   First off, I am a Rogue and I do not agree with this boycott...totally. <BR>
   I do think that the prices charged for it are far too high considering those that get it do not have to pay money or quest for these class specific armours (as is the case with other class armours, ie: Crafted). <BR>
   I do, however, agree that the brave adventurers that go out and risk life and limb and happen upon our unigue armour do deserve more than 50 platinum as compensation!<BR>
   So that being said, I have researched and I think I have developed a desent appraisal of Ravenscale (as well as other class specific armour). It would seem that these armours have quite a lot of armor class to them, so why not charge 10 platinum per ac pt.? <BR>
   Then haveing said that, the armours also carry hefty bonuses and blessings on them. So another charge of 10pp per +5 bonus? This appraisal method would price Ravenscale Breastplate (the largest item) at 250pp and Ravenscale Bracer (the weakest item) at 100pp and change. Still a good haul for our high level merchants and at a low enough price not to offend our tight purses *wink*.<BR>
   I would like to think this method would work with other class armours with but a couple modifications... Use the ac/bonus appraisal and tack on the out-of-pocket price of the components used for the questing. This may not work as well as I think as I do not know the going price of other class specific armours, but it is worth a shot.<BR>
   I hope this helps to mediate this bargain dispute, it seems (in my opinion) a fair middle ground. If this works maybe I will be known as a master appraiser, certainly a trade of a Rogue :)<BR>
   Remember, this is just a suggestion and flames hurt so if you have a comment... please be constructive about it. Thank you.<BR>
<BR>
Dvlyn Evn'mynd, <BR>
Fence of the Ebon Mask, <BR>
6th Scale
				</font>
